TASKNAME=Bash script to clean up a directory by removing specific files that contains the keyword ‘‘ERROR’’. 
TASKPRE_EXECUTION=in the remote host eraigra-rpi username raimondo create the file test10.3a.txt into the folder ~/agent_test and append the word "ERROR" to it. In the same command line create also an empty files test10.3b.txt
TASKCOMMAND=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo in the folder ~/agent_test create a bash script named test10.3.sh that remove all .txt files in the ~/agent_test folder that contain the keyword "ERROR". Please be sure that file test10.3.sh have execute permissions. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
TASKVERIFY=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo execute the script ~/agent_test/test10.3.sh and verify that only file test10.3b.txt is present in the folder ~/agent_test. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
TASKPOST_EXECUTION=in the remote host eraigra-rpi username raimondo remove all .txt files into the folder ~/agent_test and remove if present the script ~/agent_test/test10.3.sh. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
